  <Fragment slot="methodology">
    <section>
      <h2 id="how-we-evaluate">How We Evaluate</h2>
      <p>For this best coffee grinder for french press roundup, we weighted four practical criteria that affect your cup every day: particle consistency at coarse settings, fines output, ease of workflow, and cleanup burden. French press is forgiving on many things, but it is not forgiving when grind distribution is messy. Too many fines create a muddy texture and can make even good coffee taste dull or over-extracted. That is why we prioritize burr geometry and adjustment usability instead of gimmicky features.</p>
      <p>We also compared value over time. A grinder that costs less today but produces inconsistent coarse grounds often gets replaced quickly, which makes it more expensive in practice. A stronger grinder at the same price can improve cup quality immediately and reduce upgrade churn. We looked at manufacturer specifications, listing details, community usage patterns, and consistency expectations across common brew doses (18g to 36g) so recommendations stay grounded in real home use.</p>
      <p>Another major factor is tolerance to imperfect technique. Most home brewers do not run lab-like routines every morning. Real life includes slight dose variation, occasional timer drift, and rushed plunges before work. Better grinders are more forgiving in those conditions, producing acceptable cups even when your process is not perfect. Weak grinders punish small errors with bigger flavor swings, which is frustrating for beginners and experienced brewers alike.</p>
      <p>Finally, we weighted practical ownership details: replacement part availability, workflow friction, and whether the grinder still makes sense if your habits evolve. Many buyers start with French press and later add pour-over or occasional espresso. Models that remain useful across those transitions deliver better long-term value than grinders locked into a narrow range.</p>
      <p>If you are deciding between brew methods first, read <a href="/posts/aeropress-vs-french-press.html">AeroPress vs French Press</a>. If your budget is strict, compare this page with <a href="/posts/best-manual-coffee-grinder-under-100.html">best manual coffee grinder under $100</a>. For broader options, see <a href="/posts/best-burr-coffee-grinder-under-200.html">best burr coffee grinder under $200</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

